“employer” means any person who has entered into a contract of 
service to employ any other person as an employee, and includes 
an  agent,  manager  or  factor  of  such  first-mentioned  person;

“employee”  means  any  citizen  of  Malaysia  who  is  employed 
for wages under a contract of service with an employer, but does 
not  include  any  domestic  servant;

“apprentice” means a person who is undergoing a skill training 
in  a  particular  field  through  an  apprenticeship  contract  with  an 
employer  and  is  bound  to  work  in  the  employer’s  service;

(a)  to assess and determine the types and extent of employees’, 
apprentices’  and  trainees’  training  and  retraining  in 
keeping  with  the  human  resources  needs  of  industries;

(c)  to determine the terms and conditions for the making of 
grants  or  loans  from  the  Fund,  including  the  amounts 
that  may  be  approved  in  respect  of  each  application;

(e)  to organize, establish, upgrade and maintain, or to assist 
in  the  organization,  establishment,  upgrading  and 
maintenance  of,  training  facilities;

(f)  to organize and supervise, or to assist in the organization 
and supervision of, the implementation of training courses, 
projects  and  programmes;

(b)  three  persons  representing  the  Government  and  public 
sector  agencies  responsible  for  manpower  development 
or  training;

(c)  all monies earned or arising from any property, investments, 
charges,  interest  on  levy  or  debentures  acquired  by  or 
vested  in  the  Corporation;

(a)  promoting, developing and upgrading the skills of employees, 
apprentices and trainees including providing, establishing, 
expanding,  upgrading  or  maintaining  training  facilities;

(a)  the  Chairman  of  the  Board  or  the  person  for  the  time 
being  performing  the  functions  of  the  Chairman  of  the 
Board,  as  chairman;

(a)  in investments or securities authorized for the investment 
of  trust  funds  under  any  written  law  for  the  time  being 
in  force;

